She came home after a long day. Her hands trembled as her bag fell to the floor. Her body collapsed beside it, the spilled contents resembled a modern day cornucopia. Only the gun, still hot from moments before, remained in the sack on the ground. 

"Ma'am, the authorities are on their way" The voice rang in her head. She thought she was imaginging it. As her breathing slowed down though, she heard it again. Her attention now focused on the cracked phone on the floor, the memories of what she'd just done came flooding back.
